definition.value: A condition in which ejaculation is painful.
Any of various disorders affecting ejaculation.
Pain related to any of various forms of sexual function (not just sexual intercourse).
Pain related to the process of ejaculation.
Any sort of erectile behavior or process considered unhealthy or otherwise nonnormative.
A condition in which erection is painful.
Ejaculation during which the semen enters the bladder instead of the penis.
Squeezing of the urethra at the base of the penis during coitus immediately prior to ejaculation in order to induce retrograde ejaculation as a form of rudimentary contraception.
Ejaculatory behavior or activity considered within healthy boundaries.
Any sort of ejaculatory behavior or process change considered unhealthy or otherwise nonnormative.
Ejaculation in which total ejaculate volume is increased below what is considered normal and/or healthy.
Ejaculation in which total ejaculate volume is decreased below what is considered normal and/or healthy.
Spontaneity of erection considered nonnormative, unhealthy, or inappropriate.
Ejaculation in the absence of sexual stimulation for any of various reasons.
A condition in which ejaculation happens in a shorter period of time than that typically considered normal or healthy.
Any of various disorders which display premature ejaculation as a symptom.
Any sort of erectile behavior or process change considered unhealthy or otherwise nonnormative.
Increased frequency of erection considered nonnormative or unhealthy.
Decreased frequency of erection considered nonnormative or unhealthy.
Increased duration of erection considered nonnormative or unhealthy.
A condition in which ejaculation takes a prolonged period of time typically considered unnormal or unhealthy.
A transgender person who is monosexual.
A transgender person who is polysexual.
A transgender person who is gynephilic.
A transgender person who is androphilic.
An emission of biological material.
An emission produced by the penis.
An involuntary penile emission which takes place during sleep.
An emission of seminal fluid.
A penile emission which mimics seminal emission.
A member of one's extended family, i.e. outside of one's immediate family.
A member of one's immediate family, such as one's spouse, parents, siblings, and children.
A child of one of a parent's siblings or their descendents.
A child of a child.
A parent of a parent.
A child of a sibling.
A sibling of a parent.
Construction of the chest wall following damage to it or its destruction.
A caretaker and/or immediate progenitor of a child.
A spouse or other person with whom one shares a domestic, romantic or sexual bond.
A person who shares a parent.
Surgical procedures used to reconstruct, restore, or improve defective, damaged, or missing structures.
Plastic surgery to shape any of various areas of the body.
A child whose parents are in a heterosexual relationship or who are of different sexes and married to one another.
A child whose parents are in a gay relationship or who are of the same sex and married to one another.
Individual who is unable to live safely with his or her family, usually due to abuse or neglect in the family home.
A child legally belonging to particular parents who may or may not be biological parents.
Individual who becomes a child of a family by means of legal action.
A child born to their parents, being genetically related to them and/or birthed by them.
A child born to someone via the process of surrogacy.
